Turkish Stocks Gain on Bets Bank to Stop Monetary Tightening

-- B y   S e l c u k   G o k o l u k
-- 
2011-03-17T16:04:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-17/turkish-stocks-gain-on-bets-bank-to-stop-monetary-tightening.html
Turkish stocks rose for the first
day in three and the lira gained on speculation the central bank
won’t increase reserve requirements for lenders.    ISE National 100 Index (XU100)  advanced 0.3 percent to 63,482.21 at
the 5:30 p.m. close in Istanbul. The lira climbed 0.4 percent to
1.5846 per do[bn:WBTKR=XBANK:IND] llar.  The bourse’s index of banking stocks [], which make up 43
percent of the ISE National 100 Index, has fallen 5.4 percent
since the central bank increased lenders’ reserve requirements
Dec. 17 to slow credit expansion.  “The central bank may also hit the brakes on monetary
tightening,” said Serhan Yenigun, trader at Finansbank AS in
Istanbul, said in e-mailed comments.  The Turkish central bank’s
rate-setting monetary policy committee will meet on March 23.  “A conviction has emerged among investors that the central
bank will not take further steps on  reserve requirements ,” Emre Balkeser, head of trading at Garanti Investment Securities, said
in emailed comments.  Yields on two-year bonds rose 2 basis points to 8.67
percent, according to the RBS Istanbul Benchmark Bond Index.  To contact the reporters on this story:
